23:31.560 --> 23:33.260
And here are your hosts.

23:37.320 --> 23:45.240
This is David Carson. And Daryl Lane. Science fiction author Theodore Sturgeon
is justly famous as an innovator. His innovations have come in various areas,

23:45.260 --> 23:51.960
but perhaps the most important is his introduction into science fiction of
themes that had never before been treated by the genre. Right. Taboo themes,

23:52.120 --> 24:01.240
such as homosexuality and incest, among others. We asked Sturgeon if he
deliberately shattered taboos. Yes, I have purposely broken taboos. And, you

24:01.240 --> 24:11.660
know, I wrote the first stories in science fiction about homosexuality, for
example, which dealt with homosexuality and with incest. And I had a three

24:11.660 --> 24:21.700
-parter in Omni last year which dealt with cannibalism. But these stories were
not about homosexuality and about incest and about cannibalism. Essentially,

24:21.900 --> 24:30.880
they were about confrontation. All my life I've been infuriated by people who
shuck away from an idea. I don't want to hear about that. I don't, no, don't

24:30.880 --> 24:41.220
tell me that. I don't want to hear it. You know, that always angers me. Because
only by confrontation can we really learn anything. The whole history of, well,

24:41.260 --> 24:53.080
a subject like masturbation, for example, which absolutely terrified the three
or four generations before mine and preoccupied them, too. The inventor of one

24:53.080 --> 25:05.540
of our more famous breakfast foods, he was a nutritional doctor. And he used to
write dietary and medical advice books for the home. And about 75% of them has

25:05.540 --> 25:13.560
to do with masturbation and how it will make your hair fall out and give you a
softening of the brain and tuberculosis and cancer and all kinds of things.

25:15.680 --> 25:27.320
Nowadays, with a little confrontation and a little research and study, you can
read in the highest level of women's magazines not only how to do it but how to

25:27.320 --> 25:38.120
do it well. And it's become a totally accepted practice. But the horror that
went on, because people would not confront it or would not find out what the

25:38.120 --> 25:53.860
truth was, caused so much frightful damage. I mean, people committed suicide
over that. I had a relative whose whole life was absolutely made hell by his

25:53.860 --> 26:03.860
preoccupation with that. And to be tempted and be tempted and finally to yield
and then feel guilty and feel guilty and so guilty that he would never tell

26:03.860 --> 26:12.340
anybody about it. It wrecked his whole life. You know, people have got to
confront. Sturgeon has confronted many controversial or painful ideas in his

26:12.340 --> 26:20.960
novels and short stories. He continues to tell us why he does so. If we meet,
you will probably see me wearing a little silver medallion. It's a letter cute

26:20.960 --> 26:31.440
with an arrow through it. It's my trademark. And what it means is ask the next
question. To me, it's the symbol of everything that humanity has ever created.

26:32.100 --> 26:40.360
And it's the only way it has been created, by people asking the next question,
the one that follows. And so often people ask the next question, the one that

26:40.360 --> 26:47.020
follows, and the one that follows until they suddenly come to a question. They
don't want to ask because they're afraid they might get the answer. And there

26:47.020 --> 26:56.640
they stop. And when you stop asking the next question, you die. You become a
zombie and join the ranks of the zombies you see marching around you who have

26:56.640 --> 27:07.000
stopped asking the next question. It's a very symbol of life and of progress and
of science and everything toward basic truth. When you ever reach basic truth,

27:07.020 --> 27:16.900
you'll find not a thing or a precept, but you'll find a process. You'll find
something going on. And this is the way I've been thinking apparently all my

27:16.900 --> 27:26.740
life. I get very, very irritated when I find that people refuse to think beyond
a certain point. There's a bumper sticker that goes around in the Bible belt.

27:27.360 --> 27:37.480
God said it. I believe it. That settled it. When you see a bumper sticker like
that, you've just heard the crash of a closing mind. There's plenty of room out

27:37.480 --> 27:45.380
there to confront the whole idea of God and to go on with it and ask the next
question and the question that follows without committing any particular kind of

27:45.380 --> 27:45.680
sin.

